rdrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"德国諾爾德海-維斯特法倫可爾梅海姆","Merum, Limburg, Netherlands":"荷兰利包格梅盧姆","Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands":"荷兰努-布拉班特可","Limburg, Netherlands":"荷兰利包格","lifeSummary":"当Aleidis van Horne于1140年出生在荷兰利包格时，她的父亲Walter van Bemelen10岁，母亲Aleijdis van Horne16岁。她与Rutger Koenraadsz van Merum结婚。他们至少是2个儿子和2个女儿的父母。她去世于1189年享年49岁。"},"hr":{"1140–1189":"1140.–1189.","1141–1192":"1141–1192","1175–1212":"1175.–1212","1175–1235":"1175.–1235","1180–1240":"1180.–1240","1186–1242":"1186.–1242","1130–Male":"1130–preminuo","1125–1189":"1125–1189.","1242":"1242","1175":"1175.","1186":"1186.","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1141":"1141","1140":"1140.","1192":"1192","1180":"1180.","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1212":"1212","1189":"1189.","about 1175":"oko 1175.","Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Njemačka","Merum, Limburg, Netherlands":"Merum, Limburg, Nizozemska","Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Cuijk, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemska","Limburg, Netherlands":"Limburg, Nizozemska"},"cs":{"1140–1189":"1140–1189","1141–1192":"1141–1192","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1175–1235":"1175–1235","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1186–1242":"1186–1242","1130–Male":"1130–Zesnulý","1125–1189":"1125–1189","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1192":"1192","1180":"1180","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1212":"1212","1189":"1189","about 1175":"okolo 1175","Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Německo","Merum, Limburg, Netherlands":"Merum, Limburg, Nizozemsko","Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Cuijk, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemsko","Limburg, Netherlands":"Limburg, Nizozemsko"},"da":{"1140–1189":"1140–1189","1141–1192":"1141–1192","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1175–1235":"1175–1235","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1186–1242":"1186–1242","1130–Male":"1130–Afdød","1125–1189":"1125–1189","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1192":"1192","1180":"1180","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1212":"1212","1189":"1189","about 1175":"omkring 1175","Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Tyskland","Merum, Limburg, Netherlands":"Merum, Limburg, Nederlandene","Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Cuijk, Noord-Brabant, Nederlandene","Limburg, Netherlands":"Limburg, Nederlandene"},"nl":{"1140–1189":"1140–1189","1141–1192":"1141–1192","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1175–1235":"1175–1235","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1186–1242":"1186–1242","1130–Male":"1130–Overleden","1125–1189":"1125–1189","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1192":"1192","1180":"1180","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1212":"1212","1189":"1189","about 1175":"circa 1175","Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland","Merum, Limburg, Netherlands":"Merum, Limburg, Nederland","Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Cuijk, Noord-Brabant, Nederland","Limburg, Netherlands":"Limburg, Nederland"},"en":{"1140–1189":"1140–1189","1141–1192":"1141–1192","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1175–1235":"1175–1235","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1186–1242":"1186–1242","1130–Male":"1130–Deceased","1125–1189":"1125–1189","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1192":"1192","1180":"1180","1125":"1125","1235":"1235","1212":"1212","1189":"1189","about 1175":"about 1175","Merheim, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Merheim, Köln, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany","Merum, Limburg, Netherlands":"Merum, Limburg, Netherlands","Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Cuijk, North Brabant, Netherlands","Limburg, Netherlands":"Limburg, Netherlands","nameMeanings":[{"name":"van","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Anh, Thanh, Hung, Minh, Vinh, Dung, Hue, Huong, Lan, Quang, Tan, Thuy, Hong, Chi, Hang, Ho, Pok, Sang, Bai, Chin, Ching, Chu, Chuan, Dong.","Vietnamese (<b>Vạn</b>): from the Chinese surname 萬, see   Wan   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Văn</b>): from the Chinese surnames 文 or 聞, see   Wen   2 and 3, and also 5 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Wan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Yi, Qi, Qiang, Wai, Yiu, Yuk, Chien-Min, Fang, Hin, Jichun, Li, Man, Chung, Min, Yiping, Pak, Sik, Sung Man.  Vietnamese Tin, Bang, Da, Hien, Hoi, Lan, Minh Quang, Sau, Tich, Tung, Yaping, Yuet.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 萬, which means ‘ten thousand’ literally or ‘very great number’ figuratively: (i) from the personal name of Bi Wan (畢萬), an official in the state of Jin (located in present-day Shanxi province). He was said to be a descendant of Bi Gong Gao (known as Duke of Bi), the 15th son of the virtuous King Wen of Zhou (reined 1152–1056  BC ). Bi Wan was later granted the fiefdom of Wei (魏), which in 403  BC  became the state of Wei (located in present-day Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces). Some of his descendants adopted Wei (魏) as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his personal name, as their surname. (ii) from the personal name Wan (萬), style name of Rui Bo (芮伯, the Earl of Rui), an official of the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ), who was granted the fief Rui (located in Ruicheng in Shaanxi province). Some of his descendants inherited Rui (芮), the name of the fief, as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his style name, as their surname. (iii) from the placename Wan (萬), the name of a fief (located in Juxian in Shandong province) granted during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ) to an official in the ancient state of Chu. (iv) from the first element of the name of the Wan Si (萬俟) family, who lived in the downstream areas of the Yellow River during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD ). (v) from the second element of the name of the Tu Wan (吐萬) family, who are members of the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 完, meaning ‘complete’ in Chinese: (i) said to be borne by the descendants of Huan Zhui, a grandson of the Duke Huan of Song (ruler of the state of Song, died 651  BC ). (ii) from Wan (完), the name of Qu Wan (屈完), an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn Period (770–476  BC ). (iii) shortened form of the compound surname Wan-Yan (完顔), a surname from minority ethnic groups such as Juchen ethnic group in ancient northern China."]}]},{"name":"Horne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, German, and Dutch: variant of   Horn  .","Norwegian: habitational name from any of several farmsteads mostly so named from the dative singular of <i>horn</i> (see   Horn  ).","Swedish: variant of   Horn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Horn","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hershel, Emanuel, Erez, Yehuda, Ayal, Danit, Doron, Dov, Elad, Elihu, Eran, Haim.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): altered form of   Horn   5, originating under Russian influence, since Russian has no <i>h</i> and alters it to <i>g</i> in borrowed words and names. In Israel, the name has been reinterpreted by folk etymology as being from Hebrew <i>goren</i> ‘threshing floor’, which is in fact etymologically and semantically unrelated."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aleidis van Horne was born in 1140, in Limburg, Netherlands, her father, Walter van Bemelen, was 10 and her mother, Aleijdis van Horne, was 16. She married Rutger Koenraadsz van Merum. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1189, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1140–1189":"1140–1189","1141–1192":"1141–1192","1175–1212":"1175–1212","1175–1235":"1175–1235","1180–1240":"1180–1240","1186–1242":"1186–1242","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1125–1189":"1125–1189","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1141":"1141","1140":"1140